  "output": "---\n\n## Test Coverage Analysis — Pulso Backend\n\n**Current coverage: 0%.** No `#[cfg(test)]` modules, no test files, no dev-dependencies for testing.\n\n---\n\n## Untested Functions\n\n| File | Function | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| `handlers/events.rs:28` | `health_check()` | ❌ No test |\n| `handlers/events.rs:13` | `create_event()` | ❌ No test |\n| `middleware/auth.rs:15` | `require_api_key()` | ❌ No test |\n| `models/event.rs:6` | `EventInput` deserialization | ❌ No test |\n\n---\n\n## Gap Analysis by Function\n\n### `health_check()` — Simple, but still untested\n\nOnly one path exists, but it's good discipline to assert:\n- GET `/health` returns `200 OK` with body `\"OK\"`\n\n---\n\n### `require_api_key()` — 5 untested paths\n\nThis is the most complex unit with the most risk.\n\n| Scenario | Expected | Currently tested? |\n|---|---|---|\n| Missing `x-api-key` header | 401 | ❌ |\n| Header present, key not in DB | 401 | ❌ |\n| Header present, valid key | tenant injected, 200 downstream | ❌ |\n| DB error during lookup | 500 | ❌ |\n| Non-UTF8 bytes in header value | 401 | ❌ |\n| Empty string key | 401 (hash of `\"\"` won't match anything) | ❌ |\n\n**Critical missing error handling:** The SHA-256 hashing logic is untested. If someone passes a key, it gets hashed — but there's no test that the hash actually matches what was stored, meaning a misconfigured seed would silently reject all requests.\n\n---\n\n### `create_event()` — 4 untested paths + 1 bug\n\n| Scenario | Expected | Currently tested? |\n|---|---|---|\n| Valid key + valid body → event stored | 200 \"Event stored\" | ❌ |\n| Valid key + missing `event_type` field | 422 Unprocessable | ❌ |\n| Valid key + malformed JSON | 422 Unprocessable | ❌ |\n| Valid key + empty `event_type` | ❓ Currently accepted | ❌ |\n| DB insert fails | **panics** (`.expect()`) — should be 500 | ❌ |\n\n**Bug:** `create_event` uses `.expect(\"Failed to insert event\")` which will **panic** the entire server thread on a DB error. No integration test can catch this without deliberately causing a DB failure.\n\n---\n\n### `EventInput` deserialization\n\n| Scenario | Expected |\n|---|---|\n| Valid JSON `{\"event_type\": \"click\"}` | Deserializes correctly |\n| Extra unknown fields | Accepted (serde default) |\n| `event_type` is `null` | 422 |\n| `event_type` field missing entirely | 422 |\n| `event_type` is a number | 422 |\n\n---\n\n## Integration Test Gaps (Route Level)\n\nThese require a real Postgres DB (or `sqlx`'s offline mode):\n\n1. **Full auth + insert flow** — valid key → event created → row visible in DB\n2. **Tenant isolation** — tenant A cannot see tenant B's events (no GET `/events` yet, but will matter when implemented)\n3. **GET `/events` is entirely absent** — mentioned in your CLAUDE.md as a known gap for Phase 1\n\n---\n\n## Infrastructure Needed\n\nBefore writing any tests, add to `Cargo.toml`:\n\n```toml\n[dev-dependencies]\naxum-test = \"15\"          # or tower + hyper for lower-level\ntokio = { version = \"1\", features = [\"full\"] }\nsqlx = { version = \"0.9\", features = [\"runtime-tokio\", \"postgres\"] }\n```\n\nAnd you'll want a `.env.test` or `TEST_DATABASE_URL` env var pointing at a separate test DB so tests don't stomp production data.\n\n---\n\n## Test Skeletons\n\n### 1. `health_check` unit test (no DB needed)\n\n```rust\n// in handlers/events.rs, at the bottom\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n    use axum::{body::Body, http::{Request, StatusCode}, Router, routing::get};\n    use tower::ServiceExt; // for `.oneshot()`\n\n    #[tokio::test]\n    async fn health_check_returns_200() {\n        let app = Router::new().route(\"/health\", get(health_check));\n        let response = app\n            .oneshot(Request::builder().uri(\"/health\").body(Body::empty()).unwrap())\n            .await\n            .unwrap();\n\n        assert_eq!(response.status(), StatusCode::OK);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `require_api_key` — missing header → 401\n\n```rust\n// tests/auth_middleware.rs  (integration test file)\n\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn missing_api_key_returns_401() {\n    let pool = setup_test_pool().await; // helper that connects to TEST_DATABASE_URL\n    let app = build_app(pool);         // helper that wires up the full router\n\n    let response = app\n        .oneshot(\n            Request::builder()\n                .method(\"POST\")\n                .uri(\"/events\")\n                .header(\"content-type\", \"application/json\")\n                .body(Body::from(r#\"{\"event_type\":\"click\"}\"#))\n                .unwrap()\n        )\n        .await\n        .unwrap();\n\n    assert_eq!(response.status(), StatusCode::UNAUTHORIZED);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `require_api_key` — wrong key → 401\n\n```rust\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn wrong_api_key_returns_401() {\n    let pool = setup_test_pool().await;\n    let app = build_app(pool);\n\n    let response = app\n        .oneshot(\n            Request::builder()\n                .method(\"POST\")\n                .uri(\"/events\")\n                .header(\"x-api-key\", \"not-a-real-key\")\n                .header(\"content-type\", \"application/json\")\n                .body(Body::from(r#\"{\"event_type\":\"click\"}\"#))\n                .unwrap()\n        )\n        .await\n        .unwrap();\n\n    assert_eq!(response.status(), StatusCode::UNAUTHORIZED);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `create_event` — valid key + valid payload → persisted\n\n```rust\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn valid_request_stores_event() {\n    let pool = setup_test_pool().await;\n    seed_api_key(&pool, \"test-tenant\", \"my-secret-key\").await; // inserts sha256(\"my-secret-key\")\n\n    let app = build_app(pool.clone());\n\n    let response = app\n        .oneshot(\n            Request::builder()\n                .method(\"POST\")\n                .uri(\"/events\")\n                .header(\"x-api-key\", \"my-secret-key\")\n                .header(\"content-type\", \"application/json\")\n                .body(Body::from(r#\"{\"event_type\":\"page_view\"}\"#))\n                .unwrap()\n        )\n        .await\n        .unwrap();\n\n    assert_eq!(response.status(), StatusCode::OK);\n\n    // verify the row was actually written\n    let count: (i64,) = sqlx::query_as(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM events WHERE tenant_id = 'test-tenant'\")\n        .fetch_one(&pool)\n        .await\n        .unwrap();\n    assert_eq!(count.0, 1);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `create_event` — malformed JSON → 422\n\n```rust\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn malformed_json_returns_422() {\n    let pool = setup_test_pool().await;\n    seed_api_key(&pool, \"test-tenant\", \"my-secret-key\").await;\n\n    let app = build_app(pool);\n\n    let response = app\n        .oneshot(\n            Request::builder()\n                .method(\"POST\")\n                .uri(\"/events\")\n                .header(\"x-api-key\", \"my-secret-key\")\n                .header(\"content-type\", \"application/json\")\n                .body(Body::from(\"not json\"))\n                .unwrap()\n        )\n        .await\n        .unwrap();\n\n    assert_eq!(response.status(), StatusCode::UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `EventInput` deserialization unit test (no server needed)\n\n```rust\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn deserializes_valid_input() {\n        let input: EventInput = serde_json::from_str(r#\"{\"event_type\":\"click\"}\"#).unwrap();\n        assert_eq!(input.event_type, \"click\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn rejects_missing_event_type() {\n        let result: Result<EventInput, _> = serde_json::from_str(r#\"{}\"#);\n        assert!(result.is_err());\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn rejects_null_event_type() {\n        let result: Result<EventInput, _> = serde_json::from_str(r#\"{\"event_type\": null}\"#);\n        assert!(result.is_err());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Priority Order\n\n1. **Test helpers first** — `setup_test_pool()`, `build_app()`, `seed_api_key()` in `tests/helpers.rs`\n2. **`require_api_key` paths** — highest risk, auth is the security boundary\n3. **`create_event` happy path** — confirms the full stack works end-to-end\n4. **`EventInput` unit tests** — fast, no DB, highest ROI per line written\n5. **`health_check`** — trivial but good habit\n\nAlso worth fixing before tests: replace `.expect(\"Failed to insert event\")` in `create_event` with proper error handling that returns a `StatusCode::INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR`, otherwise a DB blip panics the server rather than returning a 500.\n",
